---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Industries We Serve — As-Built Company"
  description="3D laser scanning and as-built documentation for architects, general contractors, real estate, insurance, historic preservation, and facility management teams across California."
>
  <section class="hero hero-compact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">Industries</div>
      <h1>Built for the teams who <span class="accent">build.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">From architects scoping a renovation to contractors documenting progress, we tailor every deliverable to how your team actually uses it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">▲</div>
          <h3>Architects &amp; Design Firms</h3>
          <p>Survey-grade existing conditions for renovations, retrofits, and adaptive reuse. We deliver into your Revit or CAD workflow with documented accuracy &mdash; so design decisions sit on real data, not assumed dimensions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">⚒</div>
          <h3>General Contractors</h3>
          <p>Pre-construction baseline scans, milestone progress documentation, and as-built verification at handover. Reduce disputes, accelerate punch lists, and keep stakeholders aligned without flying everyone to site.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">⌂</div>
          <h3>Real Estate &amp; Brokerage</h3>
          <p>48-hour floor plans for listings, dimensioned lease drawings for commercial spaces, and 360&deg; virtual tours that work in every browser. Win listings, close deals faster.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">◉</div>
          <h3>Insurance &amp; Forensic</h3>
          <p>Pre-loss baseline documentation, post-event damage capture, and dimensioned evidence-grade records. Defensible scans for claims, litigation, and restoration planning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">◇</div>
          <h3>Historic Preservation</h3>
          <p>Non-contact documentation of fragile, protected, and irreplaceable structures. Heritage-grade records that meet documentation requirements for HABS, SHPO, and federal preservation projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">⚙</div>
          <h3>Facility &amp; Property Management</h3>
          <p>Accurate floor plans and equipment locations for operations, lease audits, space planning, and emergency response. Build a digital baseline of every property you manage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">⊞</div>
          <h3>Engineering &amp; MEP</h3>
          <p>Point cloud and BIM deliverables for mechanical, electrical, and plumbing coordination. Clash-detect against existing conditions before fabrication.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">▦</div>
          <h3>Hospitality &amp; Retail</h3>
          <p>Floor plan packages for multi-location chains, brand-standard documentation for rollouts, and pre-construction capture for redesigns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-card">
          <div class="industry-icon">+</div>
          <h3>Other Industries</h3>
          <p>Healthcare, education, industrial, government &mdash; if it has walls, a ceiling, or a footprint, we can document it. Tell us about your project.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-strip">
        <div class="text">
          <h3>Industry-specific scope?</h3>
          <p>Tell us what you need and we&rsquo;ll match the right deliverable to your workflow.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn">Get a Quote <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
